Credit Ratings
ENTERGY Corp. (New Orleans) -- Standard  Poor's Corp.
said it raised its ratings on about $1.96 billion of debt and
preferred stock of two units of this utility. The ratings on
Louisiana Power  Light Co.'s senior secured debt was raised
to triple-B-plus from triple-B and its senior unsecured debt
and preferred stock went to triple-B from triple-B-minus. New
Orleans Public Service Inc.'s senior secured debt was raised
to triple-B from triple-B- minus and its preferred stock to
triple-B-minus from double-B-plus. SP cited reduced
construction and operating budgets, lower debt, cost-control
measures and other factors for the improved ratings.